npm - global command, comes with node
npm --version , npm - v "to know version"


local dependency -use it only   in the particular project
npm i <Package name>

global dependency  -use it in any project
npm install  -g <Packagename>
sudo install -g <Packagename> (mac)

package.json- mainfest file (store important info. about project/package)
manual apporach (create package.json in the root, create properties etc)
npm init (step by step, press enter to skip )
npm init -y   (everything default )